main event: A bright-white, oval-shaped object was observed at 5,000 feet moving westward at erratic speeds for 30 minutes in Huntington, California on April 1, 1956.
interesting points: The object had characteristics of a satellite observed in the same relative position in the west.
The object moved at both very high and very slow speeds.
The sighting occurred at 0605Z during daylight conditions with clear skies and a cloud bank at 5,000 feet.
The wind aloft was 265 degrees at 10 knots.
No other objects, photographs, or additional witnesses were reported.
witnesses: one witness, Mr. Costa Mesa, age 35
photographs: no photographs were included in the report
